# tarka views — resolver-IP → provider map for the `view:` record tag.
#
# Rename to views.yaml to activate. Hot-reloaded on save. Each key is
# a provider name (matched case-insensitively against a record's
# view: tag); each value is the list of that provider's RECURSIVE
# RESOLVER IP ranges (CIDR or bare IP). A query whose SOURCE address
# (the resolver, NOT the end user) falls in one of these ranges gets
# the records tagged with that provider.
#
# A record answers a client that matches ANY of its geo OR view tags;
# with no tagged match, the untagged default records answer. So this
# is complementary to GeoDNS: set geo: for ECS-capable resolvers and
# view: for the rest, and either one hitting is enough.
#
#   www  A 203.0.113.10                      # default, everyone else
#   www  A 198.51.100.10  view: [Fastweb]    # Fastweb resolvers
#   www  A 192.0.2.10     view: [TIM, Wind]  # TIM or Wind resolvers
#
# IMPORTANT: the ranges below are PLACEHOLDERS — replace them with the
# real resolver ranges of each provider. Source them from the
# provider's autonomous systems (e.g. bgp.he.net / RIPE: search the
# ASN, take the announced prefixes that host the resolvers). Wrong
# ranges mean wrong answers, so verify before enabling.

# Fastweb:
#   - 85.18.0.0/16
#   - 93.63.0.0/16
# TIM:
#   - 212.216.0.0/16
# Wind:
#   - 212.245.0.0/16
